
[1]baikalite

   BA'IKALITE, n.[From Baikal, a lake in Northern Asia.]

   A mineral occurring in acicular prisms, sometimes long, and either
   confusedly grouped or radiating from a center. Its color is greenish,
   or yellowish white. It is regarded as a variety of Tremolite. This name
   is given also to an olive-green variety of augite and also of epidote.
